{
  "texts": [
    "In the meanwhile, requirements elicitation studies have larger datasets since it is a comprehensive task involving knowledge in multiple fields and multiple information sources.",
    "Moreover, many studies leverage the data in the open-source community, such as feature requests or live chats, to build their deep-learning models.",
    "Challenges and opportunities Challenges• Low transparency of public requirements.",
    "Unlike other software development activities, the publicly accessible data for requirements typically are small in volume and lack details.",
    "For proprietary software, since requirements reflect the delivered value of the software, organizations usually consider requirements as confidential assets and are reluctant to open them."
  ]
}